CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 21 reads: "Bowling Kings - One of the top teams bowling at the Hillvue Bowling Alleys during the past season was Whitey's. The team ended the season by winning the Steel City Bowling title.  Members of the winning aggregation are, left to right, W.P. Winston, O. Layne, W.S. Smith, W.S. Anderson, captain, and O. Hall. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Whitey's bowling team: W.P. Winston, O. Layne, William "Bill" S. Smith, holding Steel City Bowling trophy; W.S. Anderson, and Oliver Hall, posed in Hillvue Bowling Alley
